Author: STAR BIT
Title: [ANN][ICO] SBT - World-Class Decentralized Exchange
Body: ABS √ó STAR BIT¬Æ  2018 Asia Blockchain Summit (ABS) was held at Marriott Hotel in Taipei on July 2nd and 3rd. It was hosted by Congressman Jason Hsu, who dedicates to make Taiwan the future blockchain community center in Asia. Blockchain industry specialists around the world attended the summit to exchange technical information. Through this event, STAR BIT has absorbed abundant knowledge and techniques, while also promoted our STAR BIT Global Union project.    STAR BIT Global Union project provides decentralized exchange (DEX) services and technology transfer to build their own DEX for both software and hardware devices to DEX supporters. STAR BIT is set to have a worldwide targeting client base, which could integrate Taiwan‚Äôs blockchain community into a global scale.  Once the project is launched, all exchanges in the Union will be able to share the same order-pool. We can expect a dramatical increase in both amount and speed of transactions. Moreover, 50% of the daily trading fee will be rebated to the SBT holders as dividends. Potential counterparties include Australia, India, America, The Great Britain, Cambodia, and Hong Kong. South Korea and Thailand are under discussion with STAR BIT as well.  „Äê Photos of ABS„Äë   While Sway Tang, CEO of STAR BIT, was being interviewed by the press, Chang-Peng Zhao, Founder and CEO of Binance has also shared his thoughts towards STAR BIT and the blockchain community. Even though Mr. Zhao currently owns the world‚Äôs largest cryptocurrency exchange, but he remains humble and friendly. There‚Äôs a saying that goes ‚Äúpeople tend to draw close to modest people, and draw away from arrogant ones‚Äù. Perhaps, this is one of Mr. Zhao‚Äôs characteristics to make him such a successful businessman in cryptocurrency community.   STAR BIT members and Jeffrey Huang‚Ää‚Äî‚ÄäFounder of Mithril and main sponsor of ABS.   STAR BIT has a very energetic and passionate core team, which most members are born after the 90s. The team has a very innovative and business solution-oriented culture. Most attendees of the summit are around their 30s, which allows STAR BIT to communicate with them easily by speaking their language, and to further introduce its specialties and targeting goal.     STAR BIT‚Äôs booth remains loaded of people even after the summit ends. Many institutional investors have expressed high interests in the Global Union project we proposed and stayed to learn more about further details.    Many thanks to Congressman Jason Hsu for his effort by hosting this summit. STAR BIT truly appreciates this opportunity to exhibit with industry leading projects and exchange technical information and development experiences at ABS. We truly hope to promote Taiwan‚Äôs blockchain technology into the global community.

Author: STAR BIT
Title: [ANN][ICO] SBT - World-Class Decentralized Exchange
Body: STAR BIT¬ÆEX‚Äôs Trading Volume Competition    STAR BIT‚Äôs Third Wave for Extra SBT! STAR BIT will launch the ‚ÄúSTAR BIT EX‚Äôs Trading Volume Competition‚Äù event at 0:00 a.m. (UTC+8) on July 16th. Participants will be awarded from all four missions separately. STAR BIT wants to ram SBT down your throat, till you choke on it!  „ÄêMissions of the event„Äë:  <Mission One> Daily ‚Ññ1  1. Mission One period: July 16th to July 25th  2. 0.5 ETH will be awarded to the 1st and 2nd user who reaches 20 ETH volume of the daily transaction during this mission.  3 .Mission reset time: 0:00 a.m. (UTC+8)  <Mission Two> Weekly ‚Ññ1  1. Mission Two consists of four rounds: 1st Round: July 16th 0:00 a.m. to July 22nd 11:59 p.m. 2nd Round: July 23rd 0:00 a.m. to July 29th 11:59 p.m. 3rd Round: July 30th 0:00 a.m. to August 5th 11:59 p.m. 4th Round: August 6th 0:00 a.m. to August 12th 11:59 p.m.  2. Prizes will be awarded according to the transaction volume rank during each round: 1st place: 2 ETH 2nd place: 1 ETH 3rd place: 0.5 ETH 4th to 5th place: 700 SBT each user 6th to 10th place: 500 SBT each user  3. Transaction volume is calculated independently during each round.  4. If users have the same transaction volume, STAR BIT will use the transaction time as the second accordance.  For example: A and B both have 10 ETH of transaction volume, but A reaches the volume prior to B, thus A wins the prize.  <Mission Three> Overall ‚Ññ1  1. Mission Three period: July 16th 0:00 a.m. to August 12th 11:59 p.m.  2. Prizes will be awarded according to the total transaction volume rank during the trading event: 1st place: 5 ETH 2nd place: 2ETH 3rd place: 1 ETH 4th to 5th place: 0.5 ETH each user 6th to 10th place: 1000 SBT each user  3. If users have the same transaction volume, STAR BIT will use the transaction time as the second accordance.  For example: A and B both have 10 ETH of transaction volume, but A reaches the volume prior to B, thus A wins the prize.  <Mission Four> Perfect Attendance Prize  1. Mission Four period: July 16th 0:00 a.m. to August 12th 11:59 p.m. Eligible users: Users trade every day during the trading event  2. Eligible users will be awarded 500 SBT.  3. This prize is limited to 20 users, if more than 20 users qualify, STAR BIT will use the total transaction volume of each user as the second accordance.  For example: A and B are both eligible, but A has a higher transaction volume than B, thus A wins the prize.  „ÄêDescription of the event„Äë 1. To be qualified to this event, participants must register their wallet addresses on the event page.  https://www.starbitex.com/Competition 2. After submitting the application, participants must agree upon the regulations and rules of this event. 3. Participants will be awarded from all four missions separately. There is no limited number to win the prize for each user. 4. Any cheating or illegal behavior is prohibited. Once a user is found cheating or illegal, his/her qualification will be dismissed. 5. The prize will be awarded after STAR BIT‚Äôs ICO ends. Confirmed date will be declared once decided. 6. STAR BIT holds the rights of explanation and modification for this event. 7. Please feel free to contact us by email for any questions related to this event at: service@sdabi.com
